(Chief Financial Officer -- Position Description) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(MANDATE CONTEXT) Tj
T*
(This is a backfill mandate. The incumbent CFO is relocating overseas at the end of the quarter) Tj
T*
(and the board wants continuity of the finance function through the upcoming refinancing round.) Tj
T*
(Internal context: the outgoing CFO has agreed to a two-month handover window. Discretion is) Tj
T*
(requested until an offer is signed, as the departure has not yet been announced internally.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(IDEAL PROFILE) Tj
T*
(We are looking for a commercially minded, hands-on Chief Financial Officer who has already run) Tj
T*
(the finance function of a group of a similar size and complexity, and who is comfortable sitting) Tj
T*
(on the executive committee and presenting directly to the board and to external lenders.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(REPORTING STRUCTURE) Tj
T*
(The role reports to the Group Chief Executive Officer. The CFO will have five direct reports and) Tj
T*
(lead a finance organisation of roughly forty people. The role is based in Dubai, United Arab) Tj
T*
(Emirates.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(EMPLOYMENT AND PACKAGE) Tj
T*
(This is a full-time, permanent position, with a target start date of 15 September 2026. The base) Tj
T*
(salary range is AED 500,000 to AED 650,000 per month. The notice period required is three) Tj
T*
(months. Bonus target is 35 percent of base salary. LTIP: eligible for long-term incentive after) Tj
T*
(twelve months of service.) Tj
T*
(Benefits and allowances include a housing allowance, an annual home leave allowance, and school) Tj
T*
(fees for up to two children.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(CANDIDATE REQUIREMENTS) Tj
T*
(Required: significant experience reporting directly to a board and to external lenders or) Tj
T*
(investors.) Tj
T*
(Required: proven experience leading IFRS-based financial reporting and internal controls for a) Tj
T*
(group of comparable scale.) Tj
T*
(Preferred: fluency in Arabic.) Tj
T*
(Preferred: prior exposure to a debt refinancing or capital markets transaction.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(COMPETENCY WEIGHTING) Tj
T*
(On the technical side, the strongest weight should go to financial reporting and controls,) Tj
T*
(closely followed by treasury and capital markets experience, with board and investor relations) Tj
T*
(and M&A or restructuring experience carrying a somewhat smaller share each.) Tj
T*
(On the behavioural side, strategic leadership and stakeholder influence should carry the most) Tj
T*
(weight, with change management and resilience under ambiguity somewhat less heavily weighted.) Tj
